n|\n|16\n|\n|\n|\n|1\n|6\n|\n|\n|\n|25\n|\n|\n|\n!77\n!611\n!0\n!20\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\" |Total\n!90\n!2\n!2\n!6\n!3\n!4\n!17\n!4\n!15\n!105\n!12\n!77\n!13\n!6\n!92\n!4\n!23\n!25\n!89\n!5\n!6\n!15\n!colspan=2|611\n!colspan=2|20\n|}\n\n===Punjabi Infected in other States===\nThose [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]] tested corona positive in other [[Indian States]] are not Included in above statistics. But enlisted here:-\n*'''On 29 March''' a 21 years old boy from [[Patiala District]] tested corona positive in [[Ambala]], [[Haryana]] who returned from [[Nepal]].<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/patiala-reports-its-first-coronavirus-case-two-villages-sealed-62768 Patiala reports its first case of coronavirus] ''The Tribune.'' Retrieved 29 March 2020.</ref>\n\n*'''On 14 April''' He was cured and discharged from the hospital.<ref>[https://m.timesofindia.com/city/gurgaon/patiala-man-first-covid-19-case-in-ambala-discharged-from-hospital/amp_articleshow/75139161.cms&ved=0ahUKEwii8qGMg5LpAhXGH7cAHXmnBpkQyM8BCCcwAA&usg=AOvVaw2S92-WprU1R9_9GPMbnP-s&ampcf=1]</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{seealso|Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n{{Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Punjab medical cases chart}}\n===March===\n*'''9 March'''. First case was confirmed in Punjab at [[Amritsar]], a person returned from [[Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/fresh-coronavirus-cases-emerge-from-punjab-bengaluru-takes-total-to-45-11583764470103.html|title=Fresh coronavirus cases emerge from Punjab, Bengaluru; takes total to 45|date=9 March 2020|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''19 March''' a 72-year-old man in [[Punjab]] who had returned from [[Germany]] via Italy became the fourth victim of the virus in the country and first in Punjab.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/72-year-old-punjab-man-who-passed-away-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-he-had-returned-from-italy-1657432-2020-03-19|title=72-year-old Punjab man who passed away tests positive for coronavirus; he had returned from Italy|website=India Today|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''20 March'''  A third case was reported in [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]'s [[S.A.S. Nagar]] where a 68-year-old women who returned from [[United Kingdom]] tested positive.<ref>[https://www.indiatvnews.com/amp/news/india/coronavirus-positive-case-punjab-mohali-covid-19-599835 Coronavirus positive case in Mohali, Total 3 in Punjab] ''India TV''. Retrieved 20 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''21 March''' 11 more Coronavirus cases were confirmed in Punjab. 6 in [[Nawanshahar]], 3 in Mohali,<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/mohali-gets-3-more-coronavirus-cases/articleshow/74754746.cms Mohali get 3 more corona positive cases] ''Times of India''. Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref> and 2 in [[Hoshiarpur]].<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-cases-mohali-hoshiarpur-moranwali-village-amritsar-en/ Coronavirus cases in Punjab increses to 13] ''PTC NEWS''. Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref> 6 in Nawanshahar and 1 in Hoshiarpur, these are those persons who came into contact with the 72-year-old person who died on 19 March in Nawanshahr due to coronavirus.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*'''22 March''' 7 more Coronavirus cases confirmed in Nawanshahar.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/seven-more-test-positive-in-punjab-total-coronavirus-cases-now-21-in-state-official/articleshow/74758915.cms|title=Seven more test positive in Punjab|newspaper=The Economic Times|date=22 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> All these persons came into contact with the same person who died on 19 March.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*'''23 March''' Two more cases confirmed in State. One in Nawanshahar and one in Mohali.<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/india/story/two-year-old-among-two-fresh-coronavirus-cases-in-punjab-1658857-2020-03-23 Two years old among two fresh coronavirus cases in Punjab] ''India Today''. Retrieved 23 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''24 March''' 3 more cases confirmed in State and all belongs to a single family in [[Jalandhar]] and the came into contact with the same person who died on 19 March in Mohali.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-confirmed-cases-jalandhar-phillaur-mohali-curfew-en/ Coronavirus-Punja confirmed 3 cases in Jalandhar, total 26 in state] ''PTC NEWS''. Retrieved 24 March 2020.</ref> After this 3 more cases confirmed in Nawanshahr.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-confirmed-cases-nawanshahr-jalandhar-curfew-en/ 3 more cases confirmed in Nawanshahr]</ref>\n*'''25 March''' Two more cases confirmed in Punjab, First corona positive case of 54 years old woman in [[Ludhiana District]] and 1 more in Hoshiarpur.<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/panic-in-ludhiana-as-first-case-of-corona-surfaces-in-industrial-hub-60928 Panic in Ludhiana as first case of corona in Ludhiana] ''The Tribune.'' Retrieved 25 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''26 March''' a 70 years old woman tested positive in Jalandhar, 4th case in Jalandhar and 1 new case in Nawanshahar.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-confirmed-cases-nawanshahr-positive-case-jalandhar-en/ Punjab confirmed new case in Jalandhar and Nawanshahr, total tally 33] ''PTC NEWS.'' Retrieved 26 March 2020.</ref> The only corona positive patient in Amritsar recovered from the coronavirus. First recovery from coronavirus in Punjab.<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjabs-first-coronavirus-patient-cured-to-be-discharged-on-friday-61413 First coronavirus patient cured, to be discharged on Friday.] ''The Tribune.'' Retrieved 26 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''27 March''' 3 more cases confirmed in Hoshiarpur and 1 in Jalandhar.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-confirmed-cases-hoshiarpur-positive-case-jalandhar-en/ Coronavirus cases in Punjab rise to 37 after new cases reported in Jalandhar and Hoshiarpur] ''PTC NEWS.'' Retrieved 27 March 2020.</ref> One more case confirmed from Mohali where a 38-year-old women tested positive.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-hoshiarpur-positive-case-jalandhar-mohali-en/ Punjab tally rises to 38 after fresh case confirmed from Mohali.] ''PTC NEWS.'' Retrieved 27 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''29 March''' Punjab reported second death due to coronavirus where 62 years old man died who was admitted in a hospital at Amritsar, but originally from Hoshiarpur. He contacted with the person who died on 19 March.<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab-reports-second-coronavirus-death-62769 Punjab reports second death due to corona] ''The Tribune''. Retrieved 30 March 2020\n</ref>\n*'''30 March''' After the gap of two days, a 65 years old man tested positive in Mohali.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/mohali-positive-case-coronavirus-punjab-covid-19-en/ Mohali Report one more case, total tally 39 in Punjab] ''PTC NEWS.'' Retrieved 30 March 2020.</ref> One more case confirmed from Ludhiana where a 42-year-old woman tested positive in a hospital at Patiala and later on died on the same day.<ref>[https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/coronavirus-positive-woman-from-ludhiana-dies-at-hospital-punjab-s-death-toll-rises-to-3-120033001350_1.html Woman from Ludhiana died at Patiala hospital due to coronavirus.] ''Business Standard''. Retrieved 30 March 2020</ref> A 35 years old man tested positive in [[Patiala District]] who returned from [[Dubai]].<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/mohali-resident-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-punjab-tally-reaches-39-63172 New cases confirmed from Patiala, Ludhiana and Mohali, total tally 41] ''The Tribune''. Retrieved 30 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''31 March''' 65 old man died due to coronavirus who was admitted into hospital just a day before.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-mohali-death-nayagaon-covid-19-punjab-death-toll-en/ Mohali reports first death due to covid-19, death toll in Punjab 4] ''PTC NEWS''