om Hoshiarpur and 2 more from Tarn Taran District.<ref>[http://www.babushahi.com/full-news.php?id=100886&headline=Twelve-more-cases-surface-on-Tuesday,-total-count-in-Punjab-climbs-to-342 12 more cases confirmed in Punjab] ''Babushahi''. Retrieved 28 April 2020.</ref>\n*'''29 April''' 3 cases confirmed in Faridkot who returned from Nanded, Maharashtra. 11 cases confirmed in Ludhiana, out of these 7 returned from Nanded and 4 returned from Kota University in Rajasthan and 3 cases confirmed in Hoshiarpur, 8 new cases reported in Mohali, Bathinda, Nawanshahr and Patiala each reported 2 cases and Jalandhar and Sangrur each reported 1 case.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/coronavirus-punjab-new-cases-from-9-districts-including-ludhiana-mohali-faridkot-en/ 33 new cases reported in Punjab] ''PTC NEWS''. Retrieved 29 April 2020.</ref>\n*'''30 April''' Total 105 cases were confirmed. 1 case reported each in Moga, Nawanshahr, Patiala, Firozpur, 2 cases reported each in Sangrur and Ropar, 3 cases reported each in Jalandhar Muktsar and Gurdaspur, 6 cases reported Kapurthala, 7 in Tarn Taran, 13 in Mohali, 28 in Amritsar and 34 in Ludhiana.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/105-new-coronavirus-cases-in-last-24-hours-in-punjab-ludhiana-amritsar-mohali-en/ 105 new coronavirus cases in last 24 hours] ''PTC NEWS''. Retrieved 30 April 2020.</ref> Later on 14 more cases confirmed in Ludhiana, total 48 in a day.<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ludhiana/punjab-48-new-covid-19-positive-cases-reported-in-ludhiana-district/articleshow/75478126.cms 48 new covid19 positive cases reported in Ludhiana] ''Times of India''. Retrieved 30 April 2020.</ref> Amritsar district reported another covid19 cases, total 67 cases in a day.<ref>[http://www.babushahi.com/full-news.php?id=100991&headline=Amritsar:-44-more-test-positive Amritsar:67 cases in a single day] ''Babushahi''. Retrieved 30 April 2020.</ref>\n===May===\n*'''1 May''' 6 cases confirmed in Mohali, 16 in Jalandhar, 1 case each in Patiala, Moga, Fatehgarh Sahib, 4 cases in Fazilka, 9 in Amritsar and 15 cases in Firozpur.<ref>[http://www.babushahi.com/full-news.php?id=101035&headline=Punjab:-105-new-cases-reported-on-Friday Punjab tally rises to 587] ''Babushahi''. Retrieved 1 May 2020.</ref> Later 24 more cases confirmed in Patiala.<ref>[https://www.ptcnews.tv/patiala-reports-24-new-coronavirus-cases-punjab-count-crosses-600/ 24 new cases in Patiala] ''PTC NEWS (Punjabi)''. Retrieved 1 May 2020.</ref>\n\n==Response==\n===Government===\n*'''On 13 March,''' the [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] governments declared holidays in all schools and colleges till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab-schools-shut-till-march-31-to-prevent-coronavirus-spread-54917|title=Punjab Schools, colleges and universities shut till 31 March to prevent coronavirus spread|website=The Tribune|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 16 March''' Punjab government issue an advisory to close gyms, restaurants, etc.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://wap.business-standard.com/multimedia/video-gallery/general/punjab-malls-gyms-restaurants-deserted-after-advisory-on-coronavirus-101227.htm|title=Punjab malls, gyms, restaurants deserted after advisory on coronavirus|newspaper=Business Standard India}}</ref>\n*'''On 19 March''' [[Punjab School Education Board]] postponed all Board Exams of 10th and 12th classes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/education/pseb-board-exam-postponed-punjab-board-class-10-12-exams-rescheduled-over-coronavirus-covid-19-2197613%3famp=1&akamai-rum=off|title=PSEB postponed Punjab board class 10 and 12 exams|website=NDTV|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref> Punjab government also shuts down public transport in state from midnight of 20 March and prohibited gathering of more than 20 persons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/punjab-shuts-down-public-transport-to-stop-march-or-coronavirus-2197584|title=Punjab shuts down public transport|website=NDTV|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 22 March''' Punjab government declared complete Lockdown in state till 31 March 2020 except Emergency services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/india/punjab-announces-lockdown-across-the-state-till-march-31|title=Punjab announces complete lockdown till 31 March|website=National Herald India|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''On 23 March''' Punjab Government imposed full [[curfew]] across Punjab without any relaxation, become first State to impose full curfew, as some people were defy to follow lockdown, seriously.<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/full-curfew-imposed-across-punjab-no-relaxation-60035 Full curfew imposed across Punjab] ''The Tribune''. Retrieved 23 March 2020.</ref> Punjab government sanctions 20 crore rupees for free food, medicines to poor from ''CM Relief Fund'', ministers pledge month's salary for efforts to control COVID-19.<ref>[https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/punjab-minister-tript-bajwa-to-donate-month-s-salary-to-cm-s-relief-fund-for-efforts-to-control-covid-19/story-gz4vLBpDLSoiqmMLR2eqaP.html 20 Crore sanctions by Punjab CM.] ''Hindustan Times.'' Retrieved 24 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''On 24 March''' Punjab Chief Minister set up COVID Relief Fund to be utilised for the welfare of the people in distress due to Coronavirus.<ref>[https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/punjab-cm-sets-up-covid-relief-fund-120032401718_1.html Punjab CM sets up covid relief fund.] ''Business Standard.'' Retrieved 24 March 2020.</ref>\n*'''On 10 April,''' the [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] government extends curfew in state till May 1.<ref>[https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/punjab-extends-lockdown-till-april-30/articleshow/75082850.cms Punjab government extends curfew in state till May 01.] ''Economics Times.'' Retrieved 10 April 2020.</ref>\n*'''On 29 April,''' the Punjab government announced for extension of curfew for another 14 days. However, there will be relaxation for 4 hours every morning.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/economy-politics/coronavirus-india-live-updates-lockdown-extension-relaxation-gujarat-mumbai-delhi-cases-29-apr/story/402312.html|title=Coronavirus India Live Updates: Punjab extends lockdown|newspaper=Business Standard India|access-date=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Others===\nMinisters, Officers and MLAs including [[Indian National Congress]] and [[Shiromani Akali Dal]], decided to donate one month salary in Punjab Chief Minister Relief Fund,<ref>[https://www.dailypioneer.com/2020/state-editions/ministers--officers-in-punjab-to-donate-1-month-salary.html Ministers, Officers in Punjab to donate salary] ''Daily Pioneer.'' Retrieved 26 March 2020.</ref> [[Aam Aadmi Party]] MLA [[Aman Arora]] also donated 1 month salary.<ref>[https://mobile.twitter.com/AroraAmanSunam/status/1242017973922979840 AroraAmanSunam] ''mobile.twitter.com'' Retrieved 26 March 2020.</ref>[[Shiromani Gurdwara Parbandhak Committee]] also offered helping hand amid the coronavirus pandemic to treat corona positive patients at its Hospitals.<ref>[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/sgpc-offers-to-treat-corona-patients-at-its-hospitals-60948 SGPC offers to treat corona patients at its hospitals.] ''The Tribune.'' Retrieved 26 March 2020.</ref>\n\n==Expansion of Testing==\nThere are 17 hotspots identified by the State Government where 2 or more than 2 confirmed cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] are found.<ref>[http://pbhealth.gov.in/Media%20bulletin%20-%2012-04-2020.pdf Punjab Health Department press release] (PDF) ''pbhealth.gov.in''. Retrieved 13 April 2020.</ref> In these areas testing with [[Real-time polymerase chain reaction|RT-PCR]] and Rapid Kits will be done extensively at these hotspots. The details of hotspot is as follows:-\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!District \n!Area\n!Number of Cases\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Amritsar \n|Diamond Estate Colony \n|4\n|-\n| Udham Singh Nagar \n|4\n|-\n!